            "questionText": "Two gravitational wave detectors are located 3000 km apart, and a gravitational wave from a binary black hole merger is detected at the first detector 0.005 s before the second detector. Assuming that the wave travels in a straight line between the detectors, first compute the speed of the gravitational wave from these values, and then, given that the frequency of the detected waves is 100 Hz, calculate the wavelength of these gravitational waves.",
